3.5 stars;

The food at Masala House was pretty hit-or-miss. The Goat Pepper Fry ($9) and the Goat Gongura ($15) were delicious and I'd definitely come back to get these. But, I didn't love the Shrimp Chettinad ($14) or the Chicken 65 ($8). A friend described the Chicken Tikka as "okay, but nothing special". I didn't have any, but my group liked the naan. 

The service was pretty slow but since the restaurant was very new and very busy when we went this is pretty understandable.
